content: D-Day, was  73 years ago , June 6th, 1944. This is one of my favorite photos of that event. It was taken the night before, when Gen. Eisenhower visited an airfield where the 101st Airborne was about to board the planes and gliders taking them into France. His visit was to designed to cheer them up, instead it was the soldiers who cheered their commander. Ike had the burden of knowing many of the men he met would not survive the night, and as the planes took off, a correspondent saw tears in in the General's eyes.
name: Michael Gargiulo
title: Timeline Photos

content:
What I will remember about Gabe.

Talking to him about being a young naval officer in the Battle of Leyte Gulf in WW2

Walking with Gabe to subway after the Giants Parade and seeing every police officer and transit worker call out his name 

Listening to him speak out at station meetings about our commitment to news coverage 

Gabe invented what we do.  He believed in its importance as a public service. Legend is an over used term, so I will simply say Gabe was my hero.
name: Michael Gargiulo
title: Timeline Photos

Ok .. my boarding pass says "zone 1" and we're the fifth group to board ? It went 

First group: billionaires 

Second group: run of the mill hedge fund operators 

Third group : Olympic gold medalists 

Fourth group : CEO's of Fortune 500 companies

Fifth group : me , convicted felons, spies , college students.
